location.leadingComments:
Represents seconds of UTC time since Unix epoch
 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z. Must be from 0001-01-01T00:00:00Z to
 9999-12-31T23:59:59Z inclusive.

Non-negative fractions of a second at nanosecond resolution. Negative
 second values with fractions must still have non-negative nanos values
 that count forward in time. Must be from 0 to 999,999,999
 inclusive.
Address represents a physical address with coordinates
Location represents a GPS location
DeliveryPeriod represents the desired delivery time window
PackageInfo contains package physical characteristics
WorkHours represents courier working hours
Priority levels for packages
Package status
Courier status
Transport type
Delivery status (for deliver order)
Reason for not delivered
AcceptOrderCommand - Command to accept an order from OMS
AssignOrderCommand - Command to assign a package to a courier
DeliverOrderCommand - Command for courier to confirm delivery
UpdateCourierLocationCommand - Command to update courier location
RegisterCourierCommand - Command to register a new courier
GetPackagePoolCommand - Command to get package pool with filters
GetCourierPoolCommand - Command to get courier pool with filters
Pagination
SortBy options
AcceptOrderResponse - Response for AcceptOrderCommand
AssignOrderResponse - Response for AssignOrderCommand
DeliverOrderResponse - Response for DeliverOrderCommand
UpdateCourierLocationResponse - Response for UpdateCourierLocationCommand
RegisterCourierResponse - Response for RegisterCourierCommand
Package represents a package in the system
Courier represents a courier in the system
GetPackagePoolResponse - Response for GetPackagePoolCommand
GetCourierPoolResponse - Response for GetCourierPoolCommand
PaginationInfo
PackageAcceptedEvent - Event when a package is accepted into the pool
PackageAssignedEvent - Event when a package is assigned to a courier
Package details for courier notification
PackageInTransitEvent - Event when package is picked up and in transit
PackageDeliveredEvent - Event when package is successfully delivered
PackageNotDeliveredEvent - Event when package delivery failed
